In saucepan over low heat, melt butter. Add flour and cook 1 minute, stirring constantly. Gradually add half-and-half; cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly. Remove from heat; stir in pepper and cheese until melted. Cool completely, until firm. Combine egg and water, beating well. Set aside. Pour oil to a depth of 2 to 3 inches into a Dutch oven; heat to 375 degrees F. Roll 1 tablespoon cheese mixture in bread crumbs; dip in egg mixture and roll again in bread crumbs. Fry fritters in hot oil, until golden brown; drain. In saucepan, combine chili, green chilies, and chutney. Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated. To serve, spoon chili onto serving plates; arrange fritters over chili.